Alembic migrations for regin.

The Alembic environment lives in `env.py` one directory up and targets
`lib.orm.base.metadata` — the single MetaData that every SQLModel class
under `lib/orm/models/` registers on. The DB URL comes from
`lib.orm.engine._resolve_primary_url()` (the project-local SQLite file);
override for ad-hoc runs with `-x url=<override>` or `ALEMBIC_URL=`.

Common workflows
----------------

Existing install — stamp the current revision without running upgrades:

    .venv/bin/alembic stamp head

Apply all pending migrations (fresh install after `regin init`):

    .venv/bin/alembic upgrade head

Generate a new migration from SQLModel class changes:

    .venv/bin/alembic revision --autogenerate -m "<short description>"

Inspect current + pending:

    .venv/bin/alembic current
    .venv/bin/alembic history --verbose

Migration chain
---------------

- 0001_baseline.py — no-op. Anchors the revision chain at the schema
  represented by the current `db/schema.sql` (first published release).
  The pre-1.0 incremental migrations were collapsed into this baseline;
  every table/column/index they added now lives in `db/schema.sql`.

Schema changes from here forward land as new alembic revisions on top
of 0001. Keep `db/schema.sql` in sync so fresh `regin init` runs match
what `alembic upgrade head` would produce.
